passages.text: Market Insights 市场洞察

Index futures lower to start the week (S&P- 75bps/Nasd- 95bps/Russell- 100bps), following Global stocks lower. Europe is - 80bps, with Euro Tech- 160bps, and Asia- 50bs with HK tech- 125bps. All eyes on price action across AI/Mag 7 stocks today following Friday's "wobble" (Semis finished - 3%, NVDA - 3.4%, and Mag 7 - 1.4% against the backdrop of a flat S&P- Equalweight tape).

本周伊始，股指期货走低（标普- 75个基点/纳斯达克- 95个基点/罗素- 100个基点），跟随全球股市下跌。欧洲下跌- 80个基点，其中欧洲科技板块下跌- 160个基点；亚洲下跌- 50个基点，其中香港科技板块下跌- 125个基点。继上周五的“波动”之后（半导体收跌- 3%，NVDA下跌- 3.4%，而“七巨头”下跌- 1.4%，背景是标普等权重指数持平），今日市场焦点集中在人工智能及“七巨头”股票的价格走势上。

Headlines are fairly quiet across TMT. On the AI front, the Information reported leaders at Meta Superintelligence labs considering partnering with Google or OpenAI on AI features in Meta apps. Fair amount of Research across the street, with GS Research transferring Telecom Coverage to Mike Ng (AT&T, TMUS, VZ assumed BUY / ATUS, CHTR assumed SELL). Away from us, downgrades in FTNT (ms), and LRCX (ms)... and upgrades in ZS (ms), and GLW (ubs).

TMT领域整体新闻较为平静。在AI方面，据The Information报道，Meta Superintelligence实验室的领导层正在考虑与Google或OpenAI合作，将AI功能引入Meta应用。市场上有不少研究动态，高盛研究部将电信行业覆盖转移至Mike Ng (AT&T、TMUS、VZ预期为买入/ATUS、CHTR预期为卖出）。其他机构方面，FTNT（ms）和LRCX（ms）被下调评级......而ZS（ms）和GLW（ubs）被上调评级。

Meta Platforms' plans to improve the artificial intelligence features in its apps could lead the company to partner with Google or OpenAI, two of its biggest AI rivals. Leaders in Meta's new AI organization, Meta Superintelligence Labs, have discussed using Google's Gemini model to provide conversational, text- based answers to questions that users enter into Meta AI, the social media giant's main chatbot, a person familiar with the conversations said. Those leaders have also discussed using models by OpenAI to power Meta AI and other AI features in Meta's social media apps, another person familiar with the talks said.

Meta Platforms 计划提升其应用中的人工智能功能，这可能促使公司与其两大 AI 竞争对手 Google 或 OpenAI 合作。据一位知情人士透露，Meta 新成立的 AI 组织——Meta Superintelligence Labs 的领导层曾讨论使用 Google 的 Gemini 模型，为用户在 Meta AI（这家社交媒体巨头的主要聊天机器人）中输入的问题提供对话式、文本化的回答。另一位知情人士表示，这些领导层还讨论过使用 OpenAI 的模型来驱动 Meta AI 以及 Meta 社交媒体应用中的其他 AI 功能。

We assume coverage of US Telecom and Cable (8 stocks) including AT&T (T, Buy), T- Mobile (TMUS, Buy), Verizon (VZ, Buy), Charter (CHTR, Sell), Altice (ATUS, Sell), Cogent (CCOI, Neutral), Lumen (LUMN, Neutral), and Frontier (FYBR, Not Rated). We expect 2026 will likely be a pivotal year for the US telecom and cable sectors given heightened competition in consumer connectivity services (i.e., wireless and wireline). Unlike in years past where competitive responses were largely through plan pricing and wireless handset promotions, we are seeing more competitive activity through wireless and wireline bundling ("convergence"), network leadership & modernization efforts, and price- value offerings including third party services (e.g., streaming, AI). Link

We add Cadence Design Systems (CDNS), Valero Energy (VLO), McDonald's (MCD) and Walmart (WMT) to the US Conviction List, while removing Viper Energy (VNOM) and Insmed (INSM) For CDNS, a global electronic design and automation (EDA) company, Jim Schneider looks for compounding growth to be sustained through a broader range of non- traditional customers seeking out custom chip designs, with an outsized need for intellectual property (IP) solutions, which should fuel significant EPS growth through 2027 and beyond. Schneider's 2026 EPS is 6% above consensus. Link

SPX futures - 70bps // NDX - 90bps // RTY - 95bps // UST10yr +5.5bps @ 4.285% // WTI +2.95% @ \(65.90 //\) Bitcoin +1.2% @ \(11,210 as global equities trade mostly risk off with no screaming catalyst outside of decent rate moves in longer dated gov' t bonds on continued gov' t financing (esp in Europe)/inflation concerns (UST30yr +5bps @ 4.975%, 30yr Gilts highest lvl since 1998 @ \~5.69%, German 30yr bund highest lvl since 2011 @ 3.4%).

Over the weekend Turmp said India offered to cut its import tariffs to zero. Russia' s Gazprom signed a deal to build Power of Siberia 2 gas pipeline to China (BBG). Also Keep an eye on homebuilders (GS Housing Exposure = GSXUHOME) after Bessent said Trump might declare a National Housing Emergency thufall(BBG)...FTSE -45bps, CAC -10bps, DAX -1.45%, Nikkei +29bps, Hang Seng -47bps, Shanghai -45bps.

Focus today: S&P Global Manf PMI:45am), ISM Manf (10am), Construction Spending (10am), Trump scheduled to make an announcement/subject undisclosed (2pm), and no Fed speakers. ASO and SIG reopen pre- open.

\*This Week: S&P implied move through Friday (9/5) is \(1.27\%\) . Back to school week, with focus on jobs data (NFP Friday) into September FOMC meeting (mkt currently pricing in \(92\%\) chance of a 25bps cut). Busy week of conferences with GS Retail Conference Wed – Thurs in NYC (details here). Watch for headlines out of China’s leadership summit in Tianjin (through 9/1) + military parade in Beijing (9/3). Handful of earnings to keep an eye on (CRM + ASAN + AEO Wed // AVGO Thurs).

US Telecom Services and Infrastructure: Assuming coverage: Buy T, TMUS, VZ; Sell CHTR, ATUS LinkWe assume coverage of US Telecom and Cable (8 stocks) including AT&T (T, Buy), T- Mobile (TMUS, Buy), Verizon (VZ, Buy), Charter (CHTR, Sell), Altice (ATUS, Sell), Cogent (CCOI, Neutral), Lumen (LUMN, Neutral), and Frontier (FYBR, Not Rated). We expect 2026 will likely be a pivotal year for the US telecom and cable sectors given heightened competition in consumer connectivity services (i.e., wireless and wireline). Unlike in years past where competitive responses were largely through plan pricing and wireless handset promotions, we are seeing more competitive activity through wireless and wireline bundling ("convergence"), network leadership & modernization efforts, and price- value offerings including third party services (e.g., streaming, AI). Our Buy ratings on AT&T (T) and T- Mobile (TMUS) reflect our view that their investments in network modernization, spectrum, and brand will help drive the most attractive financial returns including industry leading (1) EBITDA growth; (2) free cash flow conversion; and (3) shareholder capital returns – which justify their premium EV/EBITDA valuation multiples. Our Buy rating on Verizon (VZ) is out- of- consensus, in our view; despite some tactical caution related to 3Q25E phone net additions, our positive view reflects upside to consumer wireless service revenue on waning promotional amortization headwinds and Perks contributing \(\sim 100\) bps to growth, as well the potential for better- than- expected cost & revenue synergies from the proposed acquisition of Frontier, all of which should culminate into increased shareholder capital returns through buybacks in the next 2 years (context: Verizon hasn't done any share repurchases since 2015).

We reiterate our Buy- rating and \(\) 270\(PT on Guidewire ahead of F4Q25 earnings (9/4). On the print, we are primarily focused on net new cloud deals (already tracking\) 50\% + \(ahead of typical annual pacing), FY25 ARR and fully- ramped ARR growth, and management's initial FY26 guidance. Based on the pacing of cloud deals YTD, increasing traction of deals for the full InsuranceSuite, our F4Q checks, and the timing of ARR ramps for F4Q, we believe 1) Guidewire could report an ARR beat above historical average outperformance and 2) FRARR growth has the potential to come in at\) 20\% + \(, each supporting sustained acceleration in momentum that in our view will validate Guidewire's premium in the market.

We initiate coverage of Porch Group (PRCH) with a Buy rating and 12- month price target of \(\) 21\(. Porch is a data- driven homeowners insurance, software, and consumer services platform that monetizes various components of the homebuying journey (both direct- to- consumer and B2B2C). Through Porch's existing proprietary software assets (home inspections, movers, claims) and accelerating agency distribution of homeowners insurance products under a newly formed reciprocal exchange, accelerating revenue growth and

EBITDA margin expansion lead us to be positive in what has been a growth deceleration environment for software. We believe the combination of these factors with the favorable capital position of Porch's new insurance structure creates significant upside optionality in the business, a unique dynamic that drives scarcity value in the asset.
Upgrades: GLW (Buy, UBS), SAIL (Overweight, MS), ZS (Overweight, MS)  Downgrades: FTNT (Underweight, MS), LRCX (Underweight, MS)
